name: The Goddess of Justice and Beauty of Venus, who got her from Aphrodite: LIBRA
description: She is depicted as a beautiful woman in the company of the winged cupid Eros. Many gods believed that Aphrodite's beauty could cause a war between the gods. For this reason, Zeus married Aphrodite to Hephaestus, the God of Blacksmiths, who was ugly. But despite this marriage, Aphrodite had many lovers, both divine and human.
